  <description type="morphology">Plants 5–11 cm. Stems with branches absent or few, attenuate; paraphyllia few to absent. Stem leaves (central) oblong-ovate, undulate, 2–3(–5) × 1.2–1.5 mm; margins serrulate to entire proximally, serrulate at apex; apex acute to broadly acute; ecostate or costa double, short; alar cells irregularly short-quadrate; basal laminal cells rectangular, 50–60 × 7–10 µm; distal medial cells oblong-linear, (23–)42–54 × 2–4 µm; apical cells oblong-rhombic, (15–)30–36 × (2–)3–5 µm. Sexual condition autoicous. Seta 0.1 cm. Capsule immersed.</description>
